Beverly Grace Jones (born 19 May 1948) is a Jamaican singer, actress
and model. She was born in Spanish Town, Jamaica, and raised by her
grandparents. When she was thirteen she and her siblings moved to her
parents' home in Syracuse, New York. Jones started out as a model
initially in New York state, then in Paris, working for Yves St.
Laurent, Claude Montana, and Kenzo Takada, and appearing on the covers
of Elle, Vogue, and Stern working with Helmut Newton, Guy Bourdin,
and Hans Feurer.
